               <msContents>
                  <summary>Missal, with musical notation. F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-20v: Opening Prayers, including Prayer of the Covenant, Ṣälotä Kidan, ጸሎተ፡ ኪዳን፡.  F<locus target="#21">21, </locus>-56v: Ordinary of the Mass, Śǝrǝ`atä Qǝdase,  F<locus target="#38r">38r, </locus> and v mention Abuna Basiliyos during the time he was metropolitan (1951-56), Bishop Abba Mika'el, and our king Haile Silassie (1930-1974). F<locus target="#56v">56v, </locus>-69v: Anaphora of the Apostles, Qǝdase Ḫawaryat.  F<locus target="#70r">70r, </locus>-82v: Anaphora of Our Lord, Qǝdase Ǝgzi’ǝ. F<locus target="#82v">82v, </locus>-91v: Anaphora of Mary attributed to Cyriacus of Bǝhǝnsa,  Qǝddase Maryam Gwäs’a. F<locus target="#91v">91v, </locus>-96v: Anaphora of John Chrysostom, Qǝddase Yoḥannǝs Afä Wärq, ቅዳሴ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ አፈወርቅ፡. See HSEA; EMIP 27. F<locus target="#96v">96v, </locus>-104v: Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers, Qǝddase za-Śäläsǝtu, ቅዳሴ፡ ዘሠለስቱ፡ ምዕት፡. See HSEA; EMIP 27. F<locus target="#104v">104v, </locus>-114v: Anaphora of Athanasius the Apostolic, Qǝddase Atǝnatewos, ቅዳሴ፡ አትናቴዎስ፡. F<locus target="#114v">114v, </locus>-123r: Anaphora of Basil of Caesarea, Qǝddase Baslǝyos, ቅዳሴ፡ ባስልዮስ፡. F<locus target="#123r">123r, </locus>-128v: Anaphora of Gregory, brother of Basil, Qǝddase Gorǝgorǝyos, ‘Ǝḫǝwä Baslǝyos., ቅዳሴ፡ ጎርጎርዮስ፡ እኅወ፡ ባስልዮስ፡. See HSEA; EMIP 27. Cf. Oscar Löfgren, editor, Die beiden gewöhnlichen äthiopischen Gregorius-Anaphoren. Orientalia Christiana 83–86. Rome: Pont. Institutum Orientalium Studiorum, 1933. F<locus target="#129r">129r, </locus>-135r: Anaphora of Epiphanius, Qǝddase Estifanǝyos, ቅዳሴ፡ ኤጲፋንዮስ፡. F<locus target="#135r">135r, </locus>-141r: Anaphora of Cyril of Alexandria, Qǝddase Qerǝlos, ቅዳሴ፡ ቄርሎስ፡. F<locus target="#141r">141r, </locus>-147r: Anaphora of Jacob of Serugh, Qǝddase Ya’ǝkob Zä-Śǝrug, ቅዳሴ፡ ያዕቆብ፡ ዘሥሩግ፡. See HSEA. F<locus target="#147r">147r, </locus>-149r: Anaphora of Dioscorus, Qǝddase Diosǝqoros, ቅዳሴ፡ ዲዮስቆሮስ፡.  F<locus target="#149r">149r</locus>-152r: Anaphora of Gregory, the second, Qǝddase Gorǝgorǝyos Kalǝ‘, ቅዳሴ፡ ጎርጎርዮስ፡ ካልዕ፡, also known as Anaphora of Gregory, the Wonder Worker, Qǝdase Gorǝgorǝyos, Gäbare mänkǝrat, ቅዳሴ፡ ጎርጎርዮስ፡ ገባሬ፡ መንክራት፡.</summary>
